[?2004huser@e88682a67d3d:~/scheduler$ cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'
[?2004l[?2004h> # Timezone Bug Fix Summary
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Problem
[?2004l[?2004h> The scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times for meetings between 2am-3am local time (Europe/Berlin), specifically during DST transitions. The issue only occurred when run via cron, causing a 1-hour offset.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Root Cause
[?2004l[?2004h> In `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> **OLD (BUGGY) CODE:**
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> def convert_to_berlin(utc_time_str):
[?2004l[?2004h>     utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h>     berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)  # BUG: Treats UTC time as Berlin time!
[?2004l[?2004h>     return berlin_dt
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> This incorrectly treated the parsed UTC datetime as if it were already in Berlin timezone.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Solution
[?2004l[?2004h> **NEW (FIXED) CODE:**
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> def convert_to_berlin(utc_time_str):
[?2004l[?2004h>     utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h>     utc_dt_aware = UTC_TZ.localize(utc_dt)      # First: localize as UTC
[?2004l[?2004h>     berlin_dt = utc_dt_aware.astimezone(BERLIN_TZ)  # Then: convert to Berlin
[?2004l[?2004h>     return berlin_dt
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> This properly:
[?2004l[?2004h> 1. Localizes the naive datetime as UTC
[?2004l[?2004h> 2. Converts it to Berlin timezone using `astimezone()`
[?2004l[?2004h> 3. Correctly handles DST transitions
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Example
[?2004l[?2004h> For the "Maintenance Window Prep" meeting at 2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC:
[?2004l[?2004h> - **Old (buggy):** Treated as 01:30 CET+0100 (wrong timezone)
[?2004l[?2004h> - **New (fixed):** Correctly converts to 03:30 CEST+0200
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> March 31, 2024 is when Europe/Berlin transitions from CET (UTC+1) to CEST (UTC+2) at 2am local time.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Files Modified
[?2004l[?2004h> - `/home/user/scheduler/app.py` - Fixed timezone conversion logic
[?2004l[?2004h> - Backup created at `/home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup`
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Status
[?2004l[?2004h> ✅ Fix applied and tested
[?2004l[?2004h> ✅ Crontab already installed and running
[?2004l[?2004h> ✅ Ready for Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder
